items.title: Carney Gets Down to Work as Canada Election Drumbeat Grows
items.description: (Bloomberg) -- Mark Carney laid the groundwork to take over as Canada’s prime minister as soon as this week, appointing a chief of staff and promising a speedy transition to a new cabinet that he says will be focused on the economy and fighting back against US tariffs.
